ASUS recently launched its new ZenBook Flip 13, which boasts a cutting-edge Intel 11th-generation Core i7 CPU. This high-end processor is packed into a sleek and stylish body that sports an ultra-thin bezel and a 360-degree hinge – allowing you to fold the touch display into multiple configurations. It is also extremely slim, making it a powerful and portable tool for any professional. This thin form factor and versatile design is the highlight of the ZenBook Flip 13, as it allows you to use the device as a tablet or laptop while still running a full version of Windows 10 on high-performance hardware. Additional features include a full-size HDMI port as well as two Thunderbolt 4 ports (USB Type-C layout) and a USB Type-A port. It then packs full laptop keyboard and a glass-covered precision touchpad which supports four-finger gestures and can be switched to a number pad at the press of a button. Wi-Fi 6 connectivity for blazingly-fast Internet speeds, Bluetooth 5.0 connectivity, and support for the ASUS Pen stylus then cement its role as a high-performance professional laptop. The slim design of the ZenBook Flip 13 is enabled in part by its NanoEdge 13.3-inch 1,920 x 1,080 OLED touchscreen, which needs no backlight and delivers clear and bright colours. This display is then powered by Intel Iris X graphics, which is a new feature of the Intel’s Core 11th-generation CPUs. Additionally, the ZenBook Flip 13 ships with up to 16GB of RAM, a 512GB PCIe SSD, a 50Wh battery that delivers up to 13 hours of battery life and can be charged to 60% in 49 minutes, and Harman Kardon high-quality stereo speakers. This is not all, however, as the ZenBook Flip 13 meets the ultra-demanding MIL-STD-810G military standard for reliability and durability. ASUS earned this rating after putting the ZenBook Flip 13 through extended tests in harsh environments – including extreme altitudes, temperatures, and humidity. It has also passed ASUS internal laptop tests that far exceed the standards set by the industry. Specifications and images of the new ASUS ZenBook Flip 13 are shown below. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-444888" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-1.jpg" alt="ASUS ZenBook Flip 1" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-1.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-1-300x225.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-1-1200x900.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-444898" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-6.jpg" alt="ASUS ZenBook Flip 6" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-6.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-6-300x225.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-6-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-6-768x576.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-6-1200x900.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-444896" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-5.jpg" alt="ASUS ZenBook Flip 5" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ASUS-ZenBook-Flip-5.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/upl